CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 11, 1961, pg. 24, reads: "Tan Schoolboys Dominate City Tourney - Schoolboy Cagers Roar Toward Finale... in other action, Fleming Reynolds, a Fifth Avenue High starter, is shown notching two points. All the action leads to the establishment of a 1961 Pennsylvania basketball championship.  The eventual winner in Western Pennsylvania will emerge at the Pitt Field House, within the fortnight. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Basketball game with Fifth Avenue High School player #40 Fleming Reynolds shooting basket against South Hills High School players, including #24, in gymnasium
